# Portable `src/core/` — strict rules

This folder is the **portable contract** with the future Expo/React Native app. Code here must run unchanged in Node, Next.js Server Components, Client Components, and React Native.

## Banned

- `next/*` (any).
- `react-dom`, `react-dom/client`.
- DOM globals: `window`, `document`, `localStorage`, `sessionStorage`, `navigator`, `location`, `history`.
- Tailwind CSS class strings.
- JSX (no `.tsx` markup; hooks/utilities only).
- DOM types: `HTMLElement`, `MouseEvent`, `Document`, `Window`, etc.
- Direct `fetch(` calls — go through `core/api/http.ts` wrapper.
- Imports from `app/`, `components/`, `features/`, or `lib/`.

## Allowed dependencies

- `react`, `@tanstack/react-query`, `zustand`, `zod`, `@supabase/supabase-js`, `date-fns`, `nanoid`, `lodash-es`, plus internal `core/*` imports.

## Allowed file types

- `.ts` only. `.tsx` (with JSX) is banned in `core/`.

## Adapter pattern

For anything platform-specific:

1. Define an interface in `core/adapters/<thing>.ts`.
2. Export a setter (`setStorage`, `setNetwork`, etc.).
3. Web bootstrapper provides web impl in `src/lib/bootstrap.ts`.
4. Mobile bootstrapper provides RN impl.

## Folder shape

- `core/api/` — fetch wrappers + endpoint functions.
- `core/schemas/` — Zod schemas, one file per entity.
- `core/types/` — derived types (`z.infer<>`) + supabase-generated.
- `core/queries/` — TanStack Query hooks.
- `core/stores/` — Zustand stores.
- `core/utils/` — pure functions.
- `core/constants/` — enums, compliance rules.
- `core/billing/` — capability matrix.
- `core/adapters/` — platform-specific contracts.
- `core/config/env.ts` — Zod-validated env.

## Zod-first

Define schemas first; types derived from them. Use the same schema for forms, API parsing, and tests.

## What goes IN core

- Pure business logic (compliance status calc, RRB rules, tenancy state machine).
- Validation (Zod schemas).
- API client wrappers.
- Query hooks (TanStack).
- Stores (Zustand).
- Constants / enums.

## What goes OUT of core

- UI components (use `src/components/`, `src/features/`).
- Tailwind class strings.
- `next/navigation` calls (use `src/lib/navigation.ts`).
- Server Actions (`'use server'` lives in `app/`).

## Adding a new dependency

1. Verify it's pure JS (works in Node + RN).
2. Add it to the "allowed" list in `docs/11-mobile-readiness/portable-modules.md`.
3. Pin exact version.
4. Test by running `pnpm test --project core` (Node environment).

## ESLint enforces this

If your code triggers `no-restricted-imports`, `no-restricted-globals`, `no-restricted-syntax`, or boundary rules — don't bypass with `eslint-disable`. Refactor instead.

See `docs/11-mobile-readiness/eslint-boundary-rules.md` for the full ESLint config.
